parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater/air conditioning control can cause the defogging system to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially in foggy conditions.
symptoms: The interior fan does not work
the defogging system does not work
the heater emits a smell when turned on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper system can reduce visibility while driving, increasing the risk of accidents, especially in rainy or snowy conditions.
symptoms: Windshield wipers work intermittently
windshield washer fails
windshield wiper handle switch falls off or cracks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress can cause mold growth, which can lead to unpleasant odors, health issues, and damage to the vehicle's interior and electrical systems.
symptoms: Water accumulation in doors
mold growth in doors and air vents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the rear windshield can cause glass fragments to fall onto the road, potentially causing accidents or injuries to other road users.
symptoms: Rear windshield shatters and breaks off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling and dying of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to rear-end collisions, especially when driving on highways or uphill.
symptoms: The engine stalls and dies without warning
often after driving for a certain distance or time
and may occur when shifting gears
applying brakes
or going up an incline. The vehicle may lose power
and it may take 1-2 minutes to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake vacuum power booster can cause intermittent loss of braking power, leading to increased stopping distances and potential accidents.
symptoms: Spongy brake pedal
excessive brake pedal travel
intermittent loss of braking power
vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and strand the driver. In some cases, it can also lead to property damage.
symptoms: Grinding or chattering noise upon acceleration
excessive effort required to shift gears
difficulty shifting into neutral
transmission failure while the vehicle is in motion
sudden movement of the vehicle in reverse gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loose or faulty electrical connections to the transmission can cause transmission failure, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and stranding the driver.
symptoms: Excessive effort required to shift gears
difficulty shifting into neutral
transmission failure while the vehicle is in motion.
